As everyone has a mild freak out about coronavirus, it's worth pointing out that the CDC says 6,600-17,000 people have died from the flu so far this year and between 13 million and 18 million people have been infected by the flu virus.

With so little still know about the #coronavirus, how easily it spreads between humans, case fatality rates, how big the #outbreak will get, now is a good time to plan and prepare. @CDCgov website has information https://t.co/g4GNDnGqKl, Canada: https://t.co/ficZMBdKBd https://t.co/Czu3ph0Dnu
